column1: Reconstructed value of March mean temperature at Kyoto City
801-1400 A.D. : Aono and Saito (2010): International Journal of Biometeorology, 54, 211-219
1401-1990 A.D. : Aono and Kazui (2008): International Journal of Climatology, 28, 905-914
Partly modified by Aono (2012): Chikyu Kankyo (Global Environment), 17, 21-29
Column B; Reconstructed temperature deduced from 5 or more years phenological data in each 31-year time span used for smoothing by local linear regression.
Column C; upper limit of 95% confidence intervals in smoothing procedure for temperature estimates.
Column D; lower limit of 95% confidence intervals in smoothing procedure for temperature estimates.
Column E; observed temperature, smoothed by same procedure for temperature estimates.
Column F; Urban warming bias was obscured (Using Hikone weather station as a control site).
Column G; Same as Column F, except for using Kameoka weather station as a control site..
-50.00 means no data or gap of temperature estimations.
